\begin_layout Standard
This suggestion together with the comments of referee 2 on the accuracy
 and speed of these pseudopotentials led us to test our methods for much
 larger systems than the one studied in the original version, as well as
 for distorted systems.
 We have chosen two examples, which we believe address these points: a coronene
 molecule embedded in a carbon nanotube and increasingly larger helicenes.
 The first example shows that despite the fact that of our method does not
 reach chemical accuracy in the case of highly energetical excited states
 (ionisation energies being the extreme case of an electronic excitation),
 it can be useful to determine chemical properties in large systems.
 The second example, shows that this method can help to solve highly difficult
 assignations (the determination of absolute configuration of helicenes
 is not a trivial task) in a limited time.
 It could be beneficially combined with highly efficient semi empirical
 approaches like the sTDA of Grimme and coworkers.
\end_layout

