About accuracy, we expect errors that are inherent in the method: we do
 not treat explicitely the σ electrons and the effect of their reorganisation
 can not be entirely recovered, for example in cation calculations for computing
 ionisation energies.
 For comparison, we performed all-electron calculations where the σ orbitals
 are kept frozen in the cation as they are obtained in the neutral system.
 Errors are similar as for the pseudo-systems, as expected.
 We explicitely treat this point in the paper (Sections: Pseudo-potential
 definition; All-trans-polyenes).
 However, as discussed here above, we were able to determine chemical properties
 of large systems and we were able to compute distorted systems (helicenes
 and a nanotube containing a coronene molecule, see point 4 in the answer
 to the first referee).
 Furthermore, we test the applicability of our scheme to other methods and
 we used it in the framework of the CASPT2 theory for benzene, naphtlene
 and anthracene.
 Results are added in Section: Polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons.
